But capitalism, under an impressive sleight of hand, only ever presents “more capitalism” as a solution to its discontents.
The ruling classes are simply unable to accommodate any change to the holy link between waged labor and capital.
In fact, “It is already contained in the concept of the free labourer, that he is a pauper: virtual pauper,” Marx writes.
Under capitalism, and as the current pandemic is demonstrating most emphatically, most of us exist as virtual paupers.
